from collections import Counter
t = int(input())
results = []
for i in range(t):
    n = int(input())
    arr = list(map(int, input().split()))
    c = Counter(arr)
    results.append({j: i for (i, j) in c.items()}[max(c.values())] if any(filter(lambda x: x >= 3, c.values())) else -1)
print(*results, sep='\n')
